The author of the article expresses admiration for the inspiring women they have met and emphasizes the importance of sharing their stories to inspire others. They highlight the various roles women play in society, from nurturing and teaching to leading and dreaming. However, they also acknowledge that women have been silenced and face challenges such as violence, discrimination, and the burden of household and family responsibilities. The COVID-19 pandemic has further exacerbated these challenges, causing many women to lose their jobs and forcing them to choose between their careers and caring for their children. The author argues that when women are given opportunities and fair pay, they can achieve great things and positively impact their families, communities, and economies. The United States is committed to supporting women entrepreneurs through various programs and initiatives. The author expresses gratitude to these women for their courage, innovation, and mentorship, and for making their communities and country stronger.